{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":1326,"record_hash":"sha256:2c8576cb58b3beb01b746f45442377c181949b61178d53c4d9410ff196920ee7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:46:38.108Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] --status-after is silently ignored\\\" body=\\\"The capture command writes GitMeta state but never calls begin_status_after/maybe_run_status_after, so `--json --status-after agent-session capture ...` emits a bare CaptureReport instead of the global `{result,status}` wrapper. Either wire it into the mutation status-after path or explicitly reject/document the flag for this command.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs\\\" start=270 end=280 priority=2 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] CLI journey/output coverage is missing\\\" body=\\\"The feature-gated tests stop at Clap parsing/hidden-command assertions. There is no integration test that invokes the real hidden command and checks human output, JSON shape/privacy, shell mode, missing-file errors, include-transcript behavior, or status-after behavior against the POC acceptance criteria.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/args/tests.rs\\\" start=139 end=195 priority=2 confidence=0.92}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Shell format prints prose\\\" body=\\\"Shell output currently shares the human prose path, so `-f shell agent-session capture ...` prints sentences like `Would capture 2 new Codex records for project (metadata only)`. That is not very reusable for scripts and diverges from the OutputFormat::Shell contract; split shell output into stable machine-friendly fields or explicitly choose JSON/none for this command.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/command/agent_session.rs\\\" start=35 end=69 priority=3 confidence=0.8}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Metrics are classified as Unknown\\\" body=\\\"AgentSession maps to CommandName::Unknown, so telemetry-enabled runs send a sampled generic Unknown CLI event. For this privacy-sensitive hidden command, make the choice explicit: add a dedicated command name with a deliberate sample rate, or suppress metrics for capture entirely.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/utils/metrics.rs\\\" start=212 end=213 priority=3 confidence=0.78}\\n\\n**Findings**\\n- P2: `--status-after` is accepted but ignored for `agent-session capture`. I spot-checked `--json --status-after` and got the raw `CaptureReport`, not the documented wrapper from [crates/but/src/args/mod.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/args/mod.rs:47).\\n- P2: CLI acceptance coverage is thin. The POC acceptance list requires human/JSON privacy checks and runnable CLI capture behavior in [first-poc-implementation.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:328), but only parser tests exist in `crates/but`.\\n- P3: `-f shell` currently emits human prose. That is awkward for scripts and should be made intentionally machine-readable or unsupported.\\n- P3: Metrics classification is not explicit. `Unknown` avoids naming the feature, but still emits sampled telemetry when metrics are enabled.\\n\\n**Validation**\\n- Passed: `cargo test -p but-capture`\\n- Passed: `cargo test -p but --features capture args::tests::agent_session`\\n- Spot-checked missing transcript error: it did not include the full path. JSON output included only `transcriptPathBasename`, as intended.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:46:38.108Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}